|2008||Norway requires of all companies that at least 40 percent of their board members be women.<ref name="autogenerated2000"/>
|-
|May 2008|| In Los Angeles, Diana Bijon's husband, Michael, takes her last name upon marriage, after their lawsuit led to a new California state law guaranteeing the rights of married couples and registered domestic partners to choose whichever last name they prefer.<ref name="DianaBijon">{{cite news |url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2008/05/05/us-usa-name-idUKN0541896320080505 |title=Los Angeles man wins right to use wife's last name |work=Reuters |date=2008-05-05 |access-date=2012-12-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130506055814/http://uk.reuters.com/article/2008/05/05/us-usa-name-idUKN0541896320080505 |archive-date=2013-05-06 |url-status=live }}</ref>
